# Delta Specs: fix-debt-calculation-bug

## Domain: debt-calculation

### ADDED Requirements

#### Requirement 1: Fair Remainder Distribution
The system MUST distribute remainder cents via round-robin across debtors, seeded by event/item ID for determinism. (Previously: all remainder to index 0, producing outliers like 11.58 when average is 11.548.)

##### Scenario: Five debtors with remainder (57.74€ ÷ 5)
- GIVEN item 57.74€, 5 debtors, event ID "ev1", item ID "it1"
- WHEN `SplitCalculator.calculateEqual()` computes equal shares
- THEN every share is 11.54 or 11.55 (all within 1 cent of average 11.548)
- AND no share exceeds average + 1 cent

##### Scenario: Pennies with more debtors than cents (0.03€ ÷ 5)
- GIVEN item 0.03€ and 5 debtors
- WHEN equal split is computed
- THEN exactly 3 debtors receive 0.01 and 2 receive 0.00
- AND total sum equals 0.03€

##### Scenario: Exact division (10.00€ ÷ 2)
- GIVEN item 10.00€ and 2 debtors
- WHEN equal split is computed
- THEN each debtor receives exactly 5.00€

##### Scenario: Deterministic reproducibility
- GIVEN same event ID, item ID, amount, and debtor list
- WHEN calculation runs multiple times
- THEN same indices receive remainder cents every invocation

#### Requirement 2: REAL_CONSUMPTION Settlement Mode
`SettlementEngine.computeDebtorAmounts()` MUST handle `"real_consumption"` split mode by using `expense.profileWeights` for per-debtor amounts. (Previously: no matching `when` branch, fell through to `else → calculateEqual`.)

##### Scenario: REAL_CONSUMPTION with defined weights
- GIVEN expense mode `"real_consumption"` with profileWeights {A: 23.50, B: 34.24}
- WHEN `computeDebtorAmounts(expense)` is called
- THEN returns {A: 23.50, B: 34.24}
- AND amounts match CalculatorSheet preview

##### Scenario: REAL_CONSUMPTION with empty weights
- GIVEN expense mode `"real_consumption"` and empty profileWeights
- WHEN `computeDebtorAmounts(expense)` is called
- THEN falls back to equal split among expense.debtorIds

##### Scenario: Weight sum mismatch > 0.02€
- GIVEN weights sum differs from item total by more than 0.02€
- WHEN `computeDebtorAmounts(expense)` is called
- THEN returns declared weights as-is
- AND emits a warning log with the discrepancy

