## Domain: debt-ui

### ADDED Requirements

#### Requirement 4: Multi-Debt Participant Checkboxes
A profile MAY have multiple debts to different creditors after settlement. The checkbox MUST toggle ALL debts for that profile atomically. (Previously: `onTogglePaid(debt)` toggled only `firstOrNull()` while `isPaid` checked `all`, causing permanently stuck checkboxes.)

| Scenario | GIVEN | WHEN | THEN |
|---|---|---|---|
| Multi-debt toggle | Charlie owes Alice €33.33 AND Bob €6.67 | User clicks Charlie's checkbox | ALL Charlie's debts toggle to inverse of current aggregate paid state |
| Single-debt backward compat | Profile has exactly one debt | User clicks checkbox | That single debt toggles |
| Uncheck all | All profile debts are paid | User unchecks | All debts become unpaid |
| Zero debts | Profile has no debts | — | Checkbox is hidden/disabled |
| Sync immutability | Debts list is updating | User clicks checkbox | Toggle uses immutable snapshot of debts at click time |

#### Requirement 5: Correct Total Display After Settlement
After calculation is applied, displayed totals MUST reflect the two separate concepts: total expense (immutable event cost) vs. net transfers (settlement amounts). (Previously: `pendingTotal` summed unpaid transfers, displaying a misleading value that differed from total expense.)

| Scenario | GIVEN | WHEN | THEN |
|---|---|---|---|
| CALCULATED event total | Event total €100, settlement creates €66.67 net transfers | Viewing CALCULATED event | "Total del evento" shows €100 (from snapshot.totalExpense or lastCalculationTotal) |
| CALCULATED pending label | Event state is CALCULATED | Viewing event | "Pendiente" is hidden OR relabeled as "Transferencias netas" |
| OPEN event pending | Event is OPEN, debts are expense-based amounts | Viewing event | "Pendiente" shows sum of unpaid expense debts (current behavior preserved) |

#### Requirement 6: Atomic Apply — Synchronized Debts + Event State
The apply operation MUST update debts AND event state sequentially in one coroutine, with paidTransferIndices embedded in the result. (Previously: two concurrent coroutines caused race where debts appeared before event state changed, hiding checkboxes; paidTransferIndices were computed in CalculatorSheet but never passed to apply.)

| Scenario | GIVEN | WHEN | THEN |
|---|---|---|---|
| Sequential atomic apply | User clicks "Aplicar cálculo" | Apply completes | Debts AND event state (CALCULATED) are updated BEFORE UI recomposes |
| paidTransferIndices applied | CalculationResult has paidTransferIndices=[0,2] | Apply executes | Transfers at indices 0 and 2 are saved with paid=true |
| Concurrent apply blocked | Apply in progress for event E | Second apply requested for event E | Second apply serializes behind first (mutex) or is rejected |
| Auto-scroll after apply | Apply completes and UI updates | EventDetailScreen recomposes | Auto-scrolls to settlement panel (existing behavior preserved) |

